Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula has joined operations at the De Hoek Toll Plaza in Gauteng. #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Traffic officials have taken 27 vehicles off the road on routes back from holiday destinations. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula has joined operations at the De Hoek Toll Plaza in Gauteng. Mbalula says he's alarmed by the drivers and passengers not using seat belts. "We still have a problem with people who do not fasten safety belts. Safety belts minimise fatalities and injuries." High traffic volumes back to Johannesburg are expected from this weekend. WATCH: Traffic officers prepared for holiday homecomers Law enforcement agencies are on high alert to ensure road safety and full compliance with traffic laws. Motorists are urged to be smart drivers and save lives. Watch the full interview with Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula above.